citeinfo.origin: National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Environmental Satellite, Data and Information Service (NESDIS), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)
citeinfo.title: Multichannel Seismic-Reflection Profiles Aleutian Arc and Trench, Alaska USGS Open File Reports 88-502 and 89-202

descript.abstract: In June and July 1980 and again in July and August 1981, the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) conducted reconnaissance surveys from 171 degrees W to 173 degrees E longitude along the Aleutian Arc and Trench near the islands of Atka, Amlia, Kiska, Agattu and Seguam. A total of 2880 km of 24-channel seismic-reflection data were collected on the USGS Research Vessel S.P. Lee (USGS cruise identifiers L5-80-AA and L9-81-AA). These profiles are now available for purchase from the National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC).
descript.purpose: To create a report on the MULTICHANNEL SEISMIC-REFLECTION PROFILES Aleutian Arc and Trench, Alaska USGS Open File Reports 88-502 and 89-202
